cs.NE, cs.AR, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.ET

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper describes the development of an FPGA implementation of a parallel and reconfigurable architecture for sparse neural networks capable of on-chip training and inference. 
2. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on the implementation of the architecture on an FPGA. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with neural networks, which are a key component of AI. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the efficient pipelining and parallelization of the architecture, which are important aspects of control systems. 
5. cs.ET (Embedded Systems) is another possible category as the paper describes the implementation of the architecture on an FPGA, which is a common platform for embedded systems.
